p^n=\underbrace{p\cdot p\cdot p\cdots p}_{n\text{ prime numbers}}=\underbrace{1+p+p^2+p^3+\cdots +p^{n-1}}_{\text{sum of all divisors of $p^n$ except itself}}=\frac{p^n-1}{p-1}.
\frac{p^n-1}{p-1}\leq p^n-1<p^n
p\geq 2
